        </nav>
        <div class="sp-faqx-panels" id="faq-panels">
          <div class="sp-faqx-panel active" data-cat="problems" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">How do you match bricks on older or historic homes?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">We tap into our custom-home supplier network and architectural salvage yards. If a direct match is extinct, we source the closest profile and custom-tint it to achieve a flawless aesthetic blend.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Can you match the color of my weathered mortar?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Yes. Applying stark white new mortar against aged joints ruins the look. We formulate custom mortar blends, adding specialized dyes and aggregates so the new joints look perfectly weathered on day one.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sp-faqx-panel" data-cat="cost" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Will extracting the bad bricks damage the good ones?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Not with our process. We use specialized masonry saws to cleanly sever the mortar joints around the damaged brick before gently chiseling it out, ensuring the surrounding masonry is completely protected.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Is there a minimum size for a replacement project?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">We handle everything from replacing a few dozen severely spalled bricks around a front entryway, to tearing down and rebuilding entire compromised wall sections on luxury estates.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sp-faqx-panel" data-cat="repair" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Why are the faces of my bricks flaking off (spalling)?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Spalling usually indicates water is trapped behind the veneer and freezing, blowing the face off the brick. Or, an improper, overly hard mortar was previously used. We diagnose the root cause during our assessment.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Do you fix the underlying cause of the damage?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Absolutely. If a rusting steel lintel or failed window flashing caused the bricks to crack, we must replace the lintel or flashing first. We never just cover up structural failures.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sp-faqx-panel" data-cat="process" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Will you subcontract my small repair job?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Never. Whether we are building a massive custom home or replacing 50 bricks on your facade, the work is performed exclusively by our highly trained, fully insured in-house AMS craftsmen.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Are you insured to work on multi-million dollar properties?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Yes. Our primary client base consists of luxury custom home owners. We carry $2.5 million in liability insurance to provide absolute peace of mind while we operate on your property.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
